                                functions.php), e.g. from _wp_utils.php or _utils.php, we strongly do not recommend you copy respective
                                files into the child theme, but you should create the respective functions in functions.php in the child
                                theme. This should be done so that when updating the theme, new functions from these files are available for
                                use.<br>
                                As for other files - putout templates from the folder 'templates', images from the folder 'images' etc. - to
                                make changes, copy theme into the folder 'child theme' and make changes there.
